So I'll extend my line over.

00:02:44.190 --> 00:02:48.436
So one year, maybe 10 years
is over here, 10 years.

00:02:48.436 --> 00:02:49.560
And then you have 30 years.

00:02:49.560 --> 00:02:51.760
And I'll just draw 30
years as far as I can.

00:02:51.760 --> 00:02:54.730
It's not completely to
scale, but it's my best shot.

00:02:54.730 --> 00:02:58.010
And then we plot the yield for
those different maturities.

00:02:58.010 --> 00:02:59.919
So in one month,
you have a 1% yield.

00:02:59.919 --> 00:03:01.460
So let me do up the
percentages here.

00:03:01.460 --> 00:03:05.980
So this is 1%, 2%, 3%, 4%.

00:03:05.980 --> 00:03:10.350
So on one month maturity
the yield is 1%.

00:03:10.350 --> 00:03:13.730
On three month maturity
the yield is and 1/2%.

00:03:13.730 --> 00:03:16.810
So maybe it'll be
like right over there.

00:03:16.810 --> 00:03:20.130
On one year maturity
the yield is 3%.

00:03:20.130 --> 00:03:22.690
So you plot one
year, this is 3%.

00:03:22.690 --> 00:03:26.160
Let me write it, this
is 3% right over here.

00:03:26.160 --> 00:03:29.920
This is 1.5% right over there.

00:03:29.920 --> 00:03:32.660
And the first one right
over there was 1%.

00:03:32.660 --> 00:03:35.290
And then at 10 years
it's 3 and 1/2%.

00:03:35.290 --> 00:03:38.110
So 3 and 1/2% is
right over here.

00:03:38.110 --> 00:03:40.240
And we want that to be 10 years.

00:03:40.240 --> 00:03:42.010
So I'm just plotting that point.

00:03:42.010 --> 00:03:44.310
And then that 30 years, it's 4%.

00:03:44.310 --> 00:03:48.490
So 4% is what we
get at 30 years.

00:03:48.490 --> 00:03:51.200
And if we connect the
dots and draw a curve

00:03:51.200 --> 00:03:53.425
we are giving ourselves
The Yield Curve.

00:03:57.396 --> 00:03:59.020
I don't want to make
it look like-- let

00:03:59.020 --> 00:04:01.070
me see how well I can draw it.

00:04:01.070 --> 00:04:03.980
You have a curve that might
look something like that.

00:04:03.980 --> 00:04:05.480
Just by looking at
this yield curve,

00:04:05.480 --> 00:04:09.757
you see that when you lend money
to the treasury for a longer

00:04:09.757 --> 00:04:12.340
period of time, you're going to
get a higher interest than you

00:04:12.340 --> 00:04:15.460
would for a shorter
period of time.

